					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The kind of game for which one big 8bpp plane works well is Zoop. Because of the size of its playfield (18x14 cells), it needs to use 12x14 pixels in each cell. It could have used the Puyo Pop (GBA) solution in mode 1 with two 16-color planes scrolled 12 pixels apart and then chop off the bottom row of each 8x8 pixel tile with scroll HDMA, but then that'd leave a single 4-color plane for the playfield backdrop. So instead, it renders in software to a plane that covers most of the screen. But this being an advancing-block puzzle game, most of the field isn't moving at once, except for one advancing row or column of blocks.</div>

